1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - This paper deals with the construction and exploration of three-dimensional curves, which is a topic closely related to computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the properties and enumeration of different types of three-dimensional Hilbert curves, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper presents several examples of three-dimensional Hilbert curves that can be sketched on a grid, which is a topic related to computer graphics. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper discusses the enumeration of different types of three-dimensional Hilbert curves, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) - The paper presents a notation system for distinguishing and enumerating different types of three-dimensional Hilbert curves, which involves the use of symbolic computation.
